body:
@CastielFracs , yes the 200k iteration limit was set in a recent update, but it's there in part because maDLC projects are expected to use cropping, and thus larger batch sizes, and therefore not need that many training iterations. I have very complicated videos of flying birds against messy backgrounds and never have to train more than 50k iterations at batch size of 8 (25k at batch size of 16). Yes, I would crop before creating the training dataset (but you might create a copy of the whole project as a backup before running that), and then try a higher batch size (10, or 12), then train for 50k iterations.

That loss is very good. What are the rmse following evaluation of the network? 

It's also hard to tell what could be happening without seeing the video. Can you post a screen grab of a video to GitHub? Or maybe just one of your labeled images produced by check labels?
